    "en": {
      "title": "SLTB says CPC provided sufficient fuel stocks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Sri Lanka Transport Board (SLTB) says that the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation (CPC) has provided sufficient fuel stocks to maintain public transport including school transport services.",
        "The Chairman of the SLTB Kingsley Ranawaka said that buses were operating as usual on Tuesday (28) as well.",
        "Meanwhile, the All Ceylon Private Bus Owners\u2019 Association says that the number of private buses operating on Tuesday (28) could be further reduced compared to the previous days.",
        "Cabinet green light to open Sri Lanka\u2019s Fuel Import & Retail sales market to Companies from Oil producing Nations."
      ],
